&lt;h1 id=&#34;complex-numbers-and-vector-space&#34;&gt;Complex Numbers and Vector Space&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-1--complex-number-inverse&#34;&gt;Exercise 1 : Complex Number Inverse&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suppose $a $ and $b $ are real numbers, not both 0. Find real numbers $c $ and $d $ such that&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
$$ \frac{1}{a + bi} = c + di. $$&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-2--cube-root-of-unity&#34;&gt;Exercise 2 : Cube Root of Unity&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Show that&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
$$ \frac{-1 + \sqrt{3}i}{2} $$&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
is a cube root of 1 (meaning that its cube equals 1).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
